            <title><![CDATA[Egypt’s Reme-D secures GIF backing to cut diagnostic costs by 40%]]></title>
                        <description><![CDATA[<ul>
	<li>Egypt-based biotech startup Reme-D has raised $500,000 from the Global Innovation Fund (GIF) to scale its molecular diagnostics solutions.</li>
	<li>Founded in 2022 by Salma Tammam, the company develops room-temperature PCR testing kits using nanotechnology and lyophilisation techniques.</li>
	<li>The technology eliminates cold-chain requirements, reducing diagnostic costs by up to 40% and improving reliability in low-resource settings.</li>
	<li>Reme-D currently operates across Egypt, Iraq, Sudan, and Kenya, serving 92 healthcare facilities and testing around 50,000 patients monthly.</li>
	<li>The funding will support expansion into Nigeria and Libya, production scaling, and R&amp;D in genetic diseases, oncology, and maternal health.</li>
