            <title><![CDATA[Saudi fintech AVA targets cashless growth with Plug and Play backing]]></title>
                        <description><![CDATA[<ul>
	<li>Saudi Arabia-based fintech AVA has secured an undisclosed strategic investment from Plug and Play Middle East, following its graduation from the fintech accelerator programme.</li>
	<li>Founded in 2019 by Aisha Alsaggaf, AVA develops IoT-enabled payment solutions, including SoftPOS, QR payments, and smart switches for unattended transactions.</li>
	<li>The investment will support product development and regional expansion, aligning with Saudi Arabia&rsquo;s push toward a 70% cashless economy under Vision 2030.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Press release:</strong></p>

<p>Saudi fintech startup AVA has secured an undisclosed strategic investment from Plug and Play Middle East, following its successful participation in the Plug and Play Fintech Accelerator Programme.</p>

<p>Founded in 2019, AVA specialises in IoT-enabled payment infrastructure designed to digitise unattended retail and mobility sectors. Its platform integrates SoftPOS applications, QR-based payment gateways, and smart IoT switches, enabling physical devices to accept seamless, contactless payments.</p>

<p>The company&rsquo;s technology bridges the gap between hardware and digital financial services, allowing businesses to automate transactions and access real-time data insights without relying on traditional payment terminals.</p>

<p>AVA has positioned itself as a key enabler of self-service payment ecosystems across sectors including retail, hospitality, EV charging, and automated services, supporting the growing demand for frictionless, cashless transactions.</p>

<p>The new investment will support product development and regional expansion, as AVA scales its operations in line with Saudi Arabia&rsquo;s Vision 2030 objectives to increase the adoption of digital payments.</p>

<p>The deal also highlights Plug and Play&rsquo;s continued commitment to supporting fintech innovation in the Kingdom and connecting local startups with global capital and expertise.</p>]]></description>
